esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when persistent volume usage exceeds 90% on average.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Average volume used percentage above 0.9 (90%) — critical capacity.
//
// Placeholders to replace:
// - Add volume name filter: AND `kubernetes.volume.name` IN ("data", "audit", "logs")
// - Add cluster filter: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
// - Or use as-is to monitor all volumes.
//
// What it means:
// Volume nearing capacity — may cause write failures, pod evictions, or service outages.
//
// Action needed:
// Expand volume, clean up data, or add storage capacity.
//
// Adjust threshold: 0.9 = 90%, 0.8 = 80% for earlier warning.
TS metrics-kubernetes.volume-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.volume.name` IS NOT NULL
| STATS avg_usage_pct = AVG(`kubernetes.volume.fs.used.pct`)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.volume.name`, `kubernetes.pod.name`
| WHERE avg_usage_pct > 0.9
